-- BlackRock Adds to Board With Two New Appointments
-- B y   A l e x i s   L e o n d i s
-- 2012-07-26T20:07:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/blackrock-adds-to-board-with-two-new-appointments.html
BlackRock Inc. (BLK)  added Fabrizio Freda,
chief executive officer of Estee Lauder Cos., and Jessica
Einhorn, a former dean at  Johns Hopkins University , to its board
of directors.  Freda, president and CEO of Estee Lauder since July 2009,
will join BlackRock’s board in October, the New York-based firm,
the world’s largest asset manager, said today in a statement.
Einhorn, who was dean of the university’s School of Advanced
International Studies and a former managing director at the
 World Bank , will join immediately. The appointments bring the
number of members on BlackRock’s board to 19.  “Fabrizio Freda will bring valuable insights on running a
large company with diverse worldwide operations and powerful
consumer brands, and Jessica Einhorn will add further breadth to
our Board’s diverse experience with her expertise in
international finance, economic development and public policy,”
CEO Laurence D. Fink said in the statement.  BlackRock manages $3.56 trillion in assets. Susan L.
Wagner, who retired last month from the firm after leading its
growth by overseeing purchases including the fund units of
Merrill Lynch & Co. and Barclays Plc, will also join the board
in October.  To contact the reporter on this story:
